      <T n="text">0xF98ED8E9<!--String: "When a Member's actions are hurting the Dynasty and they refuse to comply, a Dynasty Head may consider declaring that Member an <b><font color='#199C2C'>Outcast</font></b>. Outcasts have more limited impact on the Dynasty, in that their effect on Prestige is reduced (for better or for worse) and they have a harder time <b><font color='#199C2C'>Encouraging</font></b> other Dynasty Members. They also can't become Heir and lose access to Dynasty Perks.\n\nSome Outcasts may feel <b><font color='#199C2C'>Repentful</font></b> and seek to change their ways, while others may feel <b><font color='#199C2C'>Resentful</font></b> and despise the Head for tarnishing them.\n\nThe Head may remove the Outcast status at any time, but an Outcast who wishes to expedite this process could try to dig up some dirt on the Head and <b><font color='#199C2C'>Extort</font></b> them, instead. Learn more about Extortion in the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Scandals</font></b> lesson."--></T>
    </U>
